==English==
===Etymology===
From French ''[[aristocrate]]'' (a word from the French Revolution), from ''[[aristocratie]]''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈærɪstəkræt/, /əˈrɪstəkræt/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# One of the [[aristocracy]], [[nobility]], or people of rank in a community; one of a ruling class; a [[noble]] (originally in Revolutionary France).

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[aristokraatti]], [[ylimys]]

